<body style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt; background-color: #ffffff;">
<h4 style="text-align: left; font-size: 12pt; margin-top: 6.00pt; margin-bottom: 2.00pt;"><b><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 18pt; font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
	 size="5">Organization of the Instrument</font></b></h4>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">CAPI
 entry applications are almost always created in system controlled mode.
 because they take advantage of CSProâ€™s ability to use logic to determine
 the question order.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">To
 get started, it is a good idea to define sections containing sets of questions
 related to one topic. The number of sections will vary from survey to
 survey. You might need a section to begin the interview and a section
 to end the interview. You also might need some help sections with FAQ
 or roster of persons in household.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">Next
 you need to develop an order of the sections, that is the order of the
 interview. Some sections like FAQ or person roster may be independent
 of the interview sequence, and may best be placed after the last subject
 matter section or after the end of the interview section.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">Now
 with a section you need to define the order of questions. Place one item
 or several items which are related to one another on separate forms. The
 forms will be in the sequence the questions are asked.</font></p>
